3. Dialup Setup: Quick Dial Window

Use the Dialup Setup: Quick Dial window to dial out to a remote system
using the device selected in the Dialup Setup: Devices window. Enter
the phone number to dial in the Phone Number text box (this text box
is not shown for direct and Datakit connections). You also can change
the Speed, Parity, Character Size, and Duplex Mode if you need values
different than those shown by clicking on the appropriate options.

The buttons available for the Dialup Setup: Quick Dial window are:

        \k(Dial Button^^Dial ButtonQD)
        \k(Reset Button^^Reset ButtonQD)
        \k(Cancel Button^^Cancel ButtonQD)
        \k(Help Button^^Help ButtonQD)
^2^Dial Button=Dial ButtonQD
