4. Dialup Setup: Device Properties Window

Use the Dialup Setup: Device Properties window to display and change
the setup information for devices on your system. Devices are used for
accessing other systems. A device is assigned a physical port on your
computer, such as serial port 1 (also called Com1 or tty00). The type
of device (for example, Hayes modem) must be specified.

If you are creating a new entry, the default Port is Com1 and the
Device Type is Hayes. Change the port by clicking on Com1, Com2, or
Other. If you select Other, a text box appears. Enter the port for the
device in this text box.

The buttons available for the Dialup Setup: Device Properties window
are:

        \k(Apply Button^^Apply ButtonDP)
        \k(Reset Button^^Reset ButtonDP)
        \k(Cancel Button^^Cancel ButtonDP)
        \k(Help Button^^Help ButtonDP)
^2^Apply Button=Apply ButtonDP
^$390
