5. Dialup Setup: Remote System Properties Window

Use the Dialup Setup: Remote System Properties window to display and
change the setup information for remote systems accessed from your
system. The information displayed is for the item selected in the
Dialup Setup window and includes the System Name, Device Type, Speed,
Phone Number, Password, and two login sequences if Extra Options is
selected. If you are creating a new entry, the text boxes for System
Name, Phone Number, and Password are empty.

The buttons available for the Dialup Setup: Remote System Properties
window are:

        \k(Apply Button^^Apply ButtonRSP)
        \k(Reset Button^^Reset ButtonRSP)
        \k(Cancel Button^^Cancel ButtonRSP)
        \k(Help Button^^Help ButtonRSP)

More information: \k(Entering Remote System Properties)
^2^Entering Remote System Properties
^$440
5. \k{Dialup Setup: Remote System Properties Window}
   5.1 Entering Remote System Properties

The following information can be entered in the Dialup Setup: Remote
System Properties window:

   o System Name: This text box is for the name of the remote system.
     This is the name of the entry that appears in the Dialup Setup
     window.

   o Device Type: This line lets you select the type of connection to
     the remote system. The choices are Modem, Direct, and Datakit. If
     the remote system is accessed with a modem and telephone line,
     click on Modem. If the remote system is directly connected to
     your computer by a cable, click on Direct. If the remote system
     is connected by a Datakit switch, click on Datakit.

   o Speed: This line lets you select the baud rate (speed) used to
     communicate with the remote system when a modem is used. For
     example, if you are using a 2400 baud modem, click on 2400. The
     Any option allows communication at any speed the modem supports.

   o Phone Number: This text box is available only when Modem is
     selected for the Device Type option. Enter the phone number you
     want to dial when calling the remote system.

   o Destination: This text
     box is available only when Datakit is selected for the Device
     Type option. Enter the Datakit destination to which you want to
     connect.

   o Password: This text box is for the uucp password on the remote
     system. Get the password from the administrator of the remote
     system.

   o Extra Option: If you click on this box, two additional text boxes
     appear:

     - Login Sequence (1): This text box looks for the end of the
       first prompt ("in:" to match "Login:") when logging in to the
       remote system.

     - Login Sequence (2): This text box looks for the end of the
       second prompt ("word:" to match "Password:") when logging in to
       the remote system.
